orangelight.title: Display the 505 field as a list on the show page
Check for digital object linked to parent record (773$w)

comments.body:
We checked with @kelea99 the host record and a different constituent: https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog?q=9969101363506421 and the viewers where different. 
I couldn't understand why this constituent https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog/9969101283506421/ would have a viewer since I couldn't find it in figgy; https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog?q=9969101283506421 returns no results. 

@kelea99 I found the figgy object id for this '9969101283506421' constituent and  I checked in figgy:  https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/42cc0f57-eb6a-4953-9af6-40415d8ddf02 and has source identifier : [9969101283506421](https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog/9969101283506421/) This is why we see the viewer on the constituent because there is already a scanned manifest in figgy. 
I confirm that it has nothing to do with the host viewer.  

Any ideas why when I search in figgy for '9969101283506421' I get no results??

pul_library_drupal.title: Trying to update the library blogs block fails with a server error

comments.body:
One of the links in this menu has invalid attributes.  Just resetting all the invalid attributes back to default gets things working again locally:
```
 UPDATE menu_links SET options='a:1:{s:10:"attributes";a:0:{}}' WHERE mlid=2010;
```

We did the following:

1. Ran the query on staging
2. Confirmed that it's possible to list these links on staging
3. Backed up the prod database.
4. Ran the query on prod
5. Confirmed that it's possible to list these links on prod.

@VickieKarasic could you please confirm that it's acting as expected?
